{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17488693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17488693"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:52:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:52:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"508"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"508","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/508"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.09,0.69,0.16,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"508"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47372"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"508","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/508"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"508"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"32105"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"439"},{"type":"tags","id":"8850"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3008"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3402"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47372","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/47372"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 21-year-old woman presents with an uncomfortable swelling on his left eyelid. This has been present for two weeks. On examination, the following is seen (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Epidermoid cyst","Blepharitis","Chalazion","Hordeolum","Conjunctivitis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with a nodule in the left upper eyelid. This is consistent with an acutely inflamed \u003Cstrong\u003Echalazion\u003C/strong\u003E. Treatment initially involves warm compresses and lid massage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEpidermoid cyst\u003C/strong\u003E is a keratin filled nodular lesion often with a central necrotic punctum. It may also get infected. This is not seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlepharitis\u003C/strong\u003E is inflammation of the eyelid margin and is a risk factor for a chalazion. Eyelid margin inflammation is not seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHordeolum\u003C/strong\u003E is an infection of the eyelid margin hair follicle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConjunctivitis\u003C/strong\u003E is an inflammation of the conjunctiva, the clear transparent structure overlying the white sclera. It presents with erythema of the conjunctiva.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A nodular swelling under the eyelid is consistent with chalazion."],"references":["Bowling, B. (2015). Kanski\u2019s clinical ophthalmology (8th ed.). W B Saunders"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"32105"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"508"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"1806"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"1806","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/1806"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/dc81f49d-d74c-4be2-b073-58855b855ce4.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/dc81f49d-d74c-4be2-b073-58855b855ce4.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":437,"height":328}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"32105","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/32105"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-06-22T09:02:02+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-12T09:05:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"508"}},"content"